items.name: Solar Panel
items.description: The Solar Panel generatesElectricitywhen positioned in direct sunlight. Use anElectricity Toolto connect it toBenchesto provide power. Contrary to its description, the Solar Panel needs to "see" the sun itself, not just be in a sunlit area to work. The panel will only provide power if it has an unobstructed view of the sun in the sky; anything that casts a shadow on it can interfere with power production. Solar Panel can be placed underwater.

items.name: Splint

items.name: Spoiled Plants

items.name: Squash Farming Packet
items.description: The Squash Farming Packet is unlocked in theWorkshopon theSpace Stationand is equipped in the Prospectors loadout before starting a new prospect. items.name: Stabilized Exotics
items.description: Stabilized Exotics are a form of currency in theWorkshopand the stabilized state that results from processing and cleaningVolatile Raw Exoticsfound onPrometheus.

items.name: Stamina
items.description: Stamina is a power gauge that fuels many of the actions in Icarus. Using tools, sprinting, jumping, attacking, and crafting all require stamina.Status Effectscan increase or decrease max stamina or stamina regeneration. A prospector who runs out of stamina becomes exhausted and cannot perform stamina-consuming actions until they've regained a significant portion of their stamina.

items.name: Stealth

items.name: Survival Backpack
items.description: The Survival Backpack is a must need when taking long trips across Icarus, fit everything you need inside for survival! Innovative storage system that mitigates injuries.

items.name: Survival Kit
items.description: Survival Kits are aTier 3bandage that heals basic wounds, deep wounds, frostbite and heatstrokeStatus Effects. It replaces a number of basic  items, but requires considerably more materials to craft.

items.name: Survival Module
items.description: This module increases the user's resistance to cold/hot environments, reducing the damage taken from Hypothermia/Hyperthermia. It can be researched and crafted on theSpace Stationin theWorkshop. Multiple Survival Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit and will further increase the users resistance to hyperthermia/hypothermia.

items.name: Suture Kit
items.description: A Suture Kit is used to treat a Deep Wound, Hemorrhage or Exotic Deep Wound.

items.name: Synthetic Enzymes
items.description: Synthetic Enzymes are a crafted variant ofCondensed Enzymesthat can be used as fuel in aLocalized Terraforming Device. UnlikeCondensed Enzymes, the synthetic version is less potent as a fuel but does not require constructing, placing or defending aVapor Condenseron anEnzyme Geyser.

items.name: Tackle Box
items.description: The Tackle Box is a storage deployable that can be used to store a handful of lures and caught fish. Unlike other storage deployables, the Tackle Box can be picked up with items inside and does not require shelter to be used. With 3 slots forLuresand 2 slots that will halt the spoil timer of any caught fish, the Tackle Box is a handy tool for fishing adventures.

items.name: Target Dummy

items.name: Water
items.description: Water is a basic resource needed for survival on Icarus. It may be consumed by drinking from natural water sources such as lakes, streams, and pools found inCaves. Water from these natural sources is Tainted Water and has a 15% chance of causing dysentery. Water has various levels of purity depending on source and means of filtering. A status icon is displayed to indicate the type and status of water the prospector has consumed.

items.name: Water Barrel
items.description: Water Barrels are a deployable that can be connected to a water network to store 300,000 water and can output 1,000 water per second to keep the network operational.

items.name: Water Bomb
items.description: The Water Bomb is aTier 2item that will aid Prospectors in extinguishing fires. Once thrown, the Water Bomb will douse the area in water, putting out any fires. Stacks up to 5.

items.name: Water Pipe Tool
items.description: The Water Pipe Tool connects theBiofuel Water Pump/Electric Water PumptoDeployables/Water Storageto provideWater.

items.name: Water Treatment Pill
